f=Governance/sentinel/marketplace/audit-trail-design/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "audit-trail-design", selected fulfill catalog's "audit-trail-method" slot standard audit logging chain-of-custody practices. Matches catalog protocol directly: log actor/action/timestamp/basis (its who/what/when/where/why schema), immutable append-only (WORM, hash chaining, separation duties), periodic integrity checks. Chosen over marquesfelip/audit-trail-design (thinner) domain-bound variants (healthcare/HIPAA-specific). NOTES SYSTEM: source's Handoff section references home repo's skills (compliance-review, data-classification). Kept verbatim; system compliance-review equivalent sentinel's future compliance scope operator's counsel, data classification assigned any agent. regulatory retention figures (HIPAA/SOC2/PCI-DSS) illustrate method. Actual retention obligations business jurisdiction (e.g., Canadian requirements like CRA's 6-year books-and-records rule) operator-supplied inputs, file's claims. skill DESIGNS audit trails; sentinel's constitution-watch gate-bypass-detection consumers trails designed way, precedent's decision log follows immutability practices. --> · p=Design audit logging systems provide accountability, traceability, compliance evidence. Produce event catalogs, log schemas, retention policies satisfy regulatory requirements support forensic investigation. · h2:Scope Constraints=Reads system architecture, regulatory requirements, data classification outputs audit design. implement logging infrastructure access production log stores. · h2:Inputs=System architecture services audited, Regulatory requirements (from compliance review available), Data classification (which data elements Confidential/Restricted), User roles access control model, Existing logging infrastructure constraints · h2:Input Sanitization=user-provided values used commands file paths. inputs treated read-only analysis targets. · h3:Progress Checklist=Step Identify auditable events, Step Define log schema, Step Specify retention policies, Step Design immutability requirements, Step Plan access controls audit data, Step Define compliance reporting · h3:Step Identify Auditable Events=Catalog event recorded compliance, security, operational accountability: · h3:Step Identify Auditable Events=**Authentication events**: Login success/failure, logout, session creation/expiry, MFA challenges, password changes, **Authorization events**: Permission grants/revocations, role changes, access denied events, **Data access events**: Read access Restricted/Confidential data, bulk exports, API queries returning PII, **Data mutation events**: Create/update/delete sensitive records, schema migrations, bulk operations, **Consent events**: Consent granted/modified/withdrawn, privacy preference changes, **Administrative events**: Configuration changes, feature flag toggles, deployment events, user account management, **Compliance events**: Data subject requests (access, erasure, portability), breach detection, regulatory submissions · h3:Step Define Log Schema=Design consistent schema answers who/what/when/where/why event: · h3:Step Define Log Schema=**who**: Actor identity (user ID, service account, API key ID). Never log credentials tokens., **what**: Event type (enum), action performed, resource affected (type ID), before/after state mutations, **when**: Timestamp UTC (ISO 8601), millisecond precision. Clock synchronization requirements., **where**: Service name, instance ID, request (correlation), source (masked policy), geographic region, **why**: Business context operation triggered event, request path, feature context, **outcome**: Success/failure, error code applicable, affected record count · h3:Step Specify Retention Policies=Define retention based regulatory business requirements: · h3:Step Specify Retention Policies=**Regulatory minimums**: HIPAA years), SOC2 year), PCI-DSS year), financial regulations (5-7 years), **Tiered retention**: Hot storage (fast query, days) Warm storage (indexed, year) Cold storage (archived, regulatory maximum), **Deletion policy**: Audit logs deleted user data retained compliance even after user data deletion, **Cost modeling**: Estimate storage costs tier growth rate · h3:Step Design Immutability Requirements=Ensure audit records cannot tampered after creation: · h3:Step Design Immutability Requirements=**Write-once storage**: Append-only log stores, WORM storage compliance, **Integrity verification**: Hash chaining Merkle trees detect tampering gaps, **Separation duties**: Audit log administrators cannot modify log contents, **Tamper evidence**: record modified deleted, system detect alert · h3:Step Plan Access Controls Audit Data=Define who access audit records under what circumstances: · h3:Step Plan Access Controls Audit Data=**Read access**: Security team (full), compliance officers (filtered), engineering (operational only, PII), **Export controls**: Bulk export requires approval, exports themselves audited, **PII audit logs**: Mask encrypt PII fields; provide decryption authorized investigations, **Cross-team access**: Support/customer success need filtered views define scope limits · h3:Step Define Compliance Reporting=Specify reports dashboards audit data support: · h3:Step Define Compliance Reporting=**Regulatory reports**: Data subject access requests, breach timeline reconstruction, consent audit trail, **Operational dashboards**: Failed authentication trends, unusual access patterns, bulk export monitoring, **Periodic evidence**: SOC2 control evidence, HIPAA access review reports, PCI-DSS log review evidence, **Alerting**: Real-time alerts high-severity events (mass data export, privilege escalation, repeated auth failures) · h3:Step Define Compliance Reporting=**Compaction resilience**: context lost during long session, re-read Inputs section reconstruct what system analyzed, check Progress Checklist completed steps, resume earliest incomplete step. · h3:Event Catalog=\| Event Category \| Event Type \| Trigger \| Data Captured \| Retention Tier \| · h3:Event Catalog=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h3:Event Catalog=\| Authentication \| login_success \| User login \| user_id, timestamp, IP, method \| Hot 90d → Cold 1y \| · h3:Event Catalog=\| Authentication \| login_failure \| Failed login \| attempted_user, timestamp, IP, reason \| Hot 90d → Cold 1y \| · h3:Event Catalog=\| Data Access \| pii_read \| PII field accessed \| user_id, accessor_id, field, purpose \| Hot 90d → Cold 7y \| · h3:Event Catalog=\| Consent \| consent_granted \| User gives consent \| user_id, purpose, scope, version, timestamp \| Hot 90d → Cold 7y \| · h3:Event Catalog=\| ... \| ... \| ... \| ... \| ... \| · h3:Log Schema=`{ \· "event_id": "uuid-v4", \· "event_type": "enum(event_catalog)", \· "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:30:00.000Z", \· "actor": {` · h3:Retention Policy=\| Tier \| Storage Type \| Duration \| Query SLA \| Cost Model \| · h3:Retention Policy=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h3:Retention Policy=\| Hot \| Primary database / search index \| 90 days \| < 1s \| $$$  \| · h3:Retention Policy=\| Warm \| Indexed archive \| 1 year \| < 30s \| $$ \| · h3:Retention Policy=\| Cold \| Object storage (compressed) \| Regulatory max (up to 7y) \| Minutes \| $ \| · h3:Access Control Matrix=\| Role \| Read Events \| Search PII Fields \| Export \| Admin \| · h3:Access Control Matrix=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h3:Access Control Matrix=\| Security Team \| All \| Yes \| With approval \| No \| · h3:Access Control Matrix=\| Compliance Officer \| All \| Yes (masked) \| With approval \| No \| · h3:Access Control Matrix=\| Engineering \| Operational only \| No \| No \| No \| · h3:Access Control Matrix=\| Audit Log Admin \| Metadata only \| No \| No \| Yes (config, not content) \| · h2:Handoff=Hand off regulatory compliance gaps discovered during audit design compliance-review full gap analysis., Hand off data sensitivity questions data-classification audit events contain unclassified data elements. · h2:Quality Checks=auditable event category represented event catalog, Log schema captures who/what/when/where/why event type, Retention policies reference specific regulatory requirements durations, Immutability controls prevent tampering detect gaps audit trail, PII within audit logs masked encrypted controlled decryption, Access control matrix defines least-privilege access role, Compliance reporting covers required regulatory evidence outputs, Alerting defined high-severity events requiring real-time response · h2:Evolution Notes=<!-- Observations appended after use -->